\begin{center}
\underline{
\emph{SUB: Formation of \textbf{F}ree and \textbf{O}pen \textbf{S}ource \textbf{S}oftware (FOSS) cell at IIST.}}
\end{center}

As students and academicians we often find ourselves in need of software for conducting numerical experiments and analysing data. As engineers this occupies the majority of our time. In an attempt to enhance the development of science and engineering the Free Software Foundation (FSF) has introduced the concept of FOSS. FOSS is any software that is \textbf{freely licensed to be used, copied and studied}. [Refer appendix]

Keeping the above in mind, we, a group of 3$^{rd}$ year B.Tech students have come forward to set up IIST's very own FOSS cell. The main aim of the cell will be to motivate people to work for the development and propagation of FOSS. This is planned to be achieved through periodic demonstrations, workshops, installation fests, lectures etc. The cell will also promote the development of software in areas related with course work by building a repository of in-house open source tools. The amount of resources spent by the Institute on proprietary software and tools can be greatly reduced if such a cell operates efficiently. 


\section{Faculty Mentors}

