\section{Appendix}

\section{What is FOSS?}

FOSS is any software that is \textbf{freely licensed to be used, copied and studied}, while also allowing the community to change the software in any way since the  source code is openly shared. The modified or unmodified source code can also be distributed to anyone for any reason. This forms the basis of the GPL (GNU Public License) offered as a standard License for Open Source ware.
The GNU Public License offers four kinds of freedom:
\begin{itemize}
\item[] $\diamond$ Freedom to run the Program for any purpose
\item[] $\diamond$ Freedom to study how the program works
\item[] $\diamond$ Freedom to redistribute copies
\item[] $\diamond$ Freedom to improve the program and also release improvements to the public.
\end{itemize}


The main idea of FOSS is that \emph{Knowledge is a common heritage of mankind, and thus software, a form of knowledge, has to be free and accessible to all.}

\section{Why FOSS?}

The adoption of OSS will entail a series of advantages :
\begin{itemize}
\item[] $\diamond$ Lower cost
\item[] $\diamond$ Better quality code
\item[] $\diamond$ Rapid Innovation
\item[] $\diamond$ Security
\item[] $\diamond$ Community support
\item[] $\diamond$ Customizability
\item[] $\diamond$ Freedom
\end{itemize}


\section{GoI - Open Source Policy}

On 27th March 2015, The Government of India (GoI) adopted a comprehensive and supportive open source policy (\url{http://deity.gov.in/sites/upload_files/dit/files/policy_on_adoption_of_oss.pdf}). The policy requests all governmental organizations    \textbf{to prefer the use of Open Source Software(OSS)} in all central government departments and ministries, with use of Closed Source Software (CSS) only being considered as an exception with sufficient justification.

\pagebreak
\section{FOSS in Kerala - ICFOSS}

Further, in 2011 Government of Kerala setup ICFOSS (\textbf{I}nternational \textbf{C}entre for \textbf{F}ree and \textbf{O}pen \textbf{S}ource \textbf{S}oftware) aiming to make India a global leader in the Open source community. The mission of ICFOSS is to promote research and development in the area of Free and Open Source Software.

ICFOSS has agreed to colloborate with us and support us in the formation of cell.

\section{FOSS at work}


Personally, using Open Source Software has enriched our lives in terms of bettering our understanding of core research areas. The use of community driven scientific softwares, packages and libraries like \textbf{OpenFOAM, FreeFEM++, TISEAN, GSL, Armadillo} and many more has enhanced the speed of our computations and we have been able to operate much more efficiently in terms of time.

\section{Why FOSS at IIST?}

Advantages like 
\begin{itemize}
\item[] $\diamond$ Increasing interoperability
\item[] $\diamond$ Reducing costs
\item[] $\diamond$ Achieving vendor independence
\item[] $\diamond$  Reducing piracy/copyright infringements 
\item[] $\diamond$ Increasing growth of knowledge-based society
\end{itemize}
 are the compelling reasons for adopting FOSS at IIST.
